-- TAV to Add Airports in North Africa, Middle East, Europe , Sabah Reports
-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 2010-10-06T05:24:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/tav-to-add-airports-in-north-africa-middle-east-europe-sabah-reports.html
TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS, the
biggest airport terminal operator in Turkey, plans to expand its
business in North Africa, the Middle East and Eastern Europe,
Sabah said citing chief executive Sani Sener.  TAV aims to grow organically and via acquisitions in those
regions, Sener said, according to the Istanbul-based newspaper.
TAV aims to raise the passengers it serves annually to 70
million from 40 million, he said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
